Simple Email Address Validator
Description:
This Python script addressVal.py checks if an email address entered by the user contains both '@' and '.' symbols.

Features:
Validates email addresses based on presence of '@' and '.'.
Prints "Valid" if both symbols are found; otherwise, prints "Invalid".

Usage:

1.Clone the repository:
git clone <repository-url>

2.Navigate to the project directory:
cd <project-directory>

3.Run the script:
python addressVal.py
Enter an email address when prompted to see validation results.

